text: thumb Dominik Siedlaczek (born 11 March 1992) is a former Austrian decathlete. He won the gold medal in athletics at 2015 European Games in Baku, finishing 1st on 110 metres hurdles, with a personal best of 14.07. In the same year he became 9th in decathlon at the 2015 Summer Universiade in Gwangju. He won several national titles in decathlon, hurdles and high jump. In 2018 he retired from professional sports and became a dual career advisor. ==References== ==External links== *IAAF Athlete’s profile *OELV Athleten Profil Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2015 European Games Category:1992 births Category:Austrian decathletes Category:Living people Category:European Games competitors for Austria Category:European Games gold medalists for Austria Category:European Games medalists in athletics Category:Place of birth missing (living people)
